    "abstractNote": "\"It is the purpose of the present paper to prove that (1) after its introduction by Ardashir I the Persian calendar and only the Persian calendar was used in Mesopotamia down at least to 451 A.D., and (2) this holds also for the acts of Simeon bar Sabbae and puts his death on September 14. Since the calendar is inextricably bound up with various eras in the documents, we shall, therefore, discuss (I) the calendar, (II) the eras, and (III) the Passion of Simeon.\" \"1. The Great Slaughter took place on Sept. 14-24, 344 A.D. (or, to be more precise, from Friday, Sept. 14, through Sunday, Sept. 23). 2. Simeon bar Sabbae was martyred on Friday, Sept. 14, 344 A.D.\" (pp. 2; 35)",
